-----------------------------------------> Views<------------------------------------------


What Are Views in Databricks?

A View in Databricks is a virtual table created from a SQL query.

ðŸ‘‰ It does NOT store data physically.
ðŸ‘‰ It only stores the SQL logic.
ðŸ‘‰ Every time you query the view, Databricks re-runs the underlying query

Three Types of views available

1.Temporary Views
2.Global Temprorary Views
3.Persistent View (Regular SQL View)

--------------------1.Temporary View

Exists only in your current Spark session

Not visible to other users

Automatically disappears when the session ends

Example:
Python
df.createOrReplaceTempView("temp_sales")
SQL

CREATE OR REPLACE TEMP VIEW temp_sales AS
SELECT * FROM sales WHERE amount > 1000;





------------------2.Global Temporary View

Exists in a special database called global_temp

Visible across all notebooks in the same cluster/session

Disappears when the cluster shuts down
Ptyhon


Python
df.createOrReplaceGlobalTempView("global_sales")

SQL
SELECT * FROM global_temp.global_sales;

------------------3.Persistent View (Regular SQL View)

Stored in the Hive or Unity Catalog metastore

Survives cluster restarts

Visible to all users who have permissions

Behaves like a permanent virtual table


A Persisted View (also called Permanent View) is a SQL view that is stored permanently in the Metastore (Hive Metastore or Unity Catalog).

ðŸ‘‰ It does not store data
ðŸ‘‰ It stores only the SQL query definition
ðŸ‘‰ It is available to all users who have permissions
ðŸ‘‰ It survives cluster restarts


CREATE VIEW high_value_sales AS
SELECT * FROM sales WHERE amount > 5000;
